node.text: There’s nothing like a game of @uno to bring people together (before temporarily tearing them apart 😊). In June, during It Gets Better: A Digital Pride Experience, Mattel’s Herschel Canton-Hudson played a game of UNO with leaders and friends of the @itgetsbetter Project. It’s just one example of how meaningful conversations can happen over a game of UNO. #Pride month may be over, but inclusivity and unity are always important. Mattel is proud to have partnered with the It Gets Better Project to create UNO Play with Pride and to help support its mission of empowering LGBTQ+ youth.

node.text: We released our 2020 citizenship report today including updated Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) strategy and goals. “As a purpose-driven company, we take our role as a responsible corporate citizen very seriously,” said Ynon Kreiz, Chairman and CEO, Mattel. “Our updated [Evironmental,Social and Goverance] strategy serves to build upon a solid foundation and leverages additional opportunities to manage our business more sustainably in a rapidly changing world. We are aiming to have a positive influence on the world around us while continuing to execute our transformation strategy and advance our purpose to empower the next generation to explore the wonder of childhood and reach their full potential.” Head over to our Instagram Stories to see more about Mattel’s 2020 Citizenship Report from @forbes.
